## Hardware Design

[cite_start]The Smart Cat Care System is built on a modular architecture centered around the **Raspberry Pi 4 Model B**, which handles logic, pet identification, and system monitoring[cite: 13, 16].

### 1. System Architecture
The system utilizes three primary hardware subsystems to ensure reliable automated feeding:
* [cite_start]**Identification Subsystem:** Uses a **PN532 RFID/NFC Module** to detect unique pet tags[cite: 10, 17].
* [cite_start]**Actuation Subsystem:** Employs a **NEMA 17 Stepper Motor** driven by a **TMC2208 Driver** for precise food dispensing[cite: 10, 18, 19].
* [cite_start]**Monitoring Subsystem:** Utilizes a **JSN-SR04T Ultrasonic Sensor** for non-contact food level tracking[cite: 10, 20].

### 2. Wiring and Interface Protocols
[cite_start]To ensure high performance and component safety, the following interface configurations are implemented[cite: 21, 22]:

| Component | Interface | Physical Pins (GPIO) | Purpose |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **PN532 RFID** | **SPI** | MOSI (10), MISO (9), SCK (11), CE0 (8) | [cite_start]Rapid data throughput for tag detection[cite: 23, 24]. |
| **TMC2208 Driver** | **Digital/PWM** | Step (17), Direction (27) | [cite_start]Precise control of dispensing volume[cite: 25]. |
| **JSN-SR04T** | **Digital** | Trigger (23), Echo (24) | [cite_start]Measures food level distance[cite: 27, 90, 91]. |

### 3. Critical Circuit Design Features
* [cite_start]**Voltage Protection:** A **voltage divider circuit** ($1k\Omega$ and $2k\Omega$ resistors) is integrated into the JSN-SR04T Echo pin to step down the 5V signal to 3.3V, preventing damage to the Raspberry Pi GPIO ports[cite: 27].
* [cite_start]**Silent Operation:** The TMC2208 driver is configured with **1/16 micro-stepping** and "StealthChop" technology to ensure the motor operates near-silently, avoiding startling the pet during feeding[cite: 26].
* [cite_start]**Power Management:** A dual-power rail strategy is used to prevent system "Brown-outs"[cite: 120].
    * [cite_start]**12V Dedicated Supply:** Powers the NEMA 17 stepper motor[cite: 120].
    * [cite_start]**5V/3A Supply:** Powers the Raspberry Pi 4 logic[cite: 120].

### 4. Hardware Safety & Reliability
* [cite_start]**Anti-Jamming:** The hardware is designed to support software-driven counter-rotation to clear blockages in the food auger[cite: 118].
* [cite_start]**Water Resistance:** The **JSN-SR04T** sensor was selected for its durability and resistance to environmental factors within the food storage container[cite: 20].

